Setup Instructions
Using Visual Studio
Clone the Repository:

Open Visual Studio.
Go to File > Open > Project/Solution.
In the Open Project dialog, select Clone or check out code.
Enter the repository URL: https://github.com/yourusername/simple-image-gallery.git.
Click Clone.
Open the Project:

Visual Studio will open the project. If it doesn't open automatically, go to File > Open > Project/Solution and select SimpleImageGallery.sln.
Restore Dependencies:

Go to Tools > NuGet Package Manager > Package Manager Console.
Run dotnet restore to install the necessary dependencies.
Build the Solution:

Go to Build > Build Solution or press Ctrl+Shift+B.
Ensure the build succeeds with no errors.
Run the Application:

Press F5 or click the Start button in Visual Studio.
The application will launch in your default web browser, typically at https://localhost:5001.
Navigate to the Gallery:

Open your browser and go to https://localhost:5001/Gallery/Index to access the image gallery.
Using Visual Studio Code
Clone the Repository:

Open Visual Studio Code.
Open the integrated terminal (`Ctrl+``).
Run git clone https://github.com/yourusername/simple-image-gallery.git.
Navigate to the project folder: cd simple-image-gallery.
Open the Project:

Open the project folder in Visual Studio Code by selecting File > Open Folder and choosing the cloned repository folder.
Restore Dependencies:

In the terminal, run dotnet restore to install the necessary dependencies.
Build the Solution:

Run dotnet build in the terminal.
Ensure the build completes successfully.
Run the Application:

Use the terminal to run dotnet run.
The application will be available at https://localhost:5001.
Navigate to the Gallery:

Open your browser and go to https://localhost:5001/Gallery/Index to access the image gallery.
